It is impossible to measure exactly 4 liters using a 6-liter jug and a 12-liter jug. This is because the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the jug capacities (6 and 12) is 6. Any amount that can be measured must be a multiple of the GCD. Since 4 is not a multiple of 6, it cannot be achieved through any sequence of filling, emptying, or pouring between the jugs.

The possible amounts that can be in the 6-liter jug are 0 or 6 liters, and in the 12-liter jug are 0, 6, or 12 liters. No combination of these states can result in 4 liters in either jug.

\boxed{\text{impossible}}
